        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Fort Oglethorpe, or
near Ringgold, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Ringgold, Fort Oglethorpe, Chickamauga, Tunnel Hill, Chattanooga
Valley, La Fayette, Noble, Lakeview, Indian Springs, Wood Station,
Graysville, Blue Spring, Fairview, Boynton, Beaumont, and Rock
Spring.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
